I used this recipe for a 5-6 bone 4# loin roast. I added lemon zest, a tablespoon of lemon juice, and olive oil to my rub. Started the meat at room temp and seared at 450 for 30 minutes. Then I turned the oven down to 340 degrees for approx 40 minutes and let it stand for 20 minutes. The roast was cooked to perfection - tender and juicy.

Rating: 4
I've been searching for this recipe! Ever since we were served the most incredible pork roast for lunch a couple of years ago during a visit to Vinci in Tuscany, I've tried numerous methods and recipes to replicate that meal and THIS IS IT! It appears that the high heat and taking care not to overcook is the secret. I changed the herb mixture slightly - adding 2 small fresh bay leaves, the zest from one small lemon and binding it with olive oil (I was told by the chef's daughter what ingredients were in their mix). I poured some chicken stock over it at the 1/2 hour point, when I turned the roast and took it out of the oven when it reached 145 F and rested it for 10 minutes. Served it with roast potatoes, carrots and brussel sprouts, drizzling the precious drippings over the meat. FABULOUS! I will make this again (and again!)

