Delicious! I did take the advice of one of the other reviewers who said to add a little olive oil to the spices and salt and wrap in plastic wrap and marinate over night and another reviewer who suggested adding the chicken broth, wine, mustard and lemon juice to the pan juices to make the au jus; it just gave it a little extra boost - real nice! Will definitely make again!

Rating: 4
Great recipe - Simple, delicious and extremely moist. For those of you who want a nice little jus try this: Combine 1/2 cup white wine and 1/2 cup low salt chicken broth in a non-reactive pan. Boil until reduced somewhat - about 6-8 minutes. Remove from heat and whisk in 1 tablespoon dijon mustard and the juice of one lemon. Season with freshly ground pepper. Reserve. After removing pork from pan, deglaze pan with the reserved lemon/wine/mustard mixture. After pork has rested, pour any accumulated juices into lemon/wine/mustard mixture and simmer for a few minutes. Taste for seasonings. Note: be careful about seasoning with additional salt - Pork is already seasoned with salt. Enjoy!

