Rating: 4
I've made this twice and IT IS GREAT. Here is my take on how to make it even better 1) definitely marinate (the first time i marinated overnight but the next time I only marinated for 4 hours--just as good) 2) for the paste--blend in olive oil to make it moister and help it to cling to the pork. 2) double the garlic and rosemary--and use fresh rosemary!! 3)At two points during the cooking, pour some chicken broth and a dash of white wine on top of the lion--REALLY makes it much more moist and flavorful. 4) watch the cooking times! Both times I made this I found it needed about 1/3 less time in the oven to be perfectly cooked (both according to the thermometer reading and the way it looked when I cut into the middle to check)

