Based on some of the earlier comments I played with the recipe a bit. I included more garlic, added some olive oil to the garlic/rosemary mixture and applied the mixture to the roast an hour before I put it in the oven. I don't usually use much salt but this recipe benefits from a generous amount. Following an earlier suggestion, once I stripped the rosemary leaves off the stem, I use the stems to create a "bed" for the roast in the pan. Finally, I cut a couple of baking potatos into quarters (lengthwise), then cut those in half again, tossed them in some of the remaining garlic/rosemay mixture and roasted them with the pork. I agree... this recipe is better than it looks on paper.

